<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-0799 </DOCNO><TEXT>Describes a device designed to run along rail tracks above coal bunkersand to collect coal that failed to drop from rail wagons, through tracksand into bunkers. The device scoops up coal and crushes it so that itcan drop through rail tracks. It has 4 wheels, is driven by an electricmotor, weighs 22 t owing to steel and concrete ballasting and normallyruns at 2.5 km/h. Device will save 1 staff member; the estimated costof 120,000 Czechoslovak crowns should therefore be recouped in less thana year.</TEXT></DOC>